The forest was dark, the only light coming from the thin sliver of moon above. Tara walked cautiously, her footsteps muffled by the thick undergrowth. Every so often, she paused, straining her ears for any sound—any sign that she wasn’t alone. She had heard the stories, of course, but she hadn’t believed them. Not until now. The wind picked up, carrying with it the scent of something wild, something ancient. Tara’s heart raced as the shadows seemed to shift around her, closing in.